@model IEnumerable<SoberModel.sp_GetSpotlightFacilities_Result>
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Treatment and Housing Directory Search";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Master.cshtml";
}
@section includes
{
    @Scripts.Render("~/bundles/profile_scripts")
    @Styles.Render("~/content/profile_css")
}
<div class="search-header">
    <div class="container">
        @Html.Partial("_SearchArea")
    </div>
</div>

<div class="content white-bg">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="faq">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading"><h4>Treatment Center Specialities</h4></div>
            </div>
            <ul class="row faq-list">
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Adolescent Treatment Centers", "adolescent_treatment", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>Since kids don’t come with instructions, parents often wonder what is best. www.sober.com helps console the uncertainty. Treatment centers and housing options in this category are specifically tailored to the special needs of teens and youth.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Alternative (Non-12 Step) Treatment", "alternative_treatment", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>Alternative Drug Treatment Programs are non 12-step based drug treatment programs that often follow a socio-educational or cognitive behavioral approach to treating addictions. The vast majority of treatment options in America are geared around 12 Step (e.g., AA, NA) programs, but if these programs aren't a good fit for you our Alternative direct is the right place to find alternative options!</p>

                </li>
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Drug & Alcohol Detox Centers ", "detox_centers", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>This is the beginning of change. Search here to find available social and medical drug and alcohol detox centers who specialize in this important first step to recovery. </p>
                </li>
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Drugs & Alcohol Treatment Clinics", "drug_alcohol", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>Not sure which category is best to find treatment for you or a loved one? Since most if not all of the facilities in our directory provide some form of treatment for drug and alcohol abuse, search here to find over 10,000 D&A treatment centers, recovery houses, coaches, counselors, and doctors ready to help.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Eating Disorders Clinics", "eating_disorders", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>Need treatment for anorexia, bulimia, or binge eating? Our comprehensive list of ED facilities who specialize exclusively in curing you or your loved one of these challenging disease is a great resource to find the help you need.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Exclusive Drug Rehabs", "exclusive_rehabs", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>Exclusive Rehabs are designed for the executive clientele that provide upscale living accommodations in a luxurious setting, with amenities that include, private suites, gourmet cooking, massage therapy, acupuncture, yoga, and much more.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Extended Care Facilities", "extended_care", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>Search for extended care facilities that offer continuing treatment after primary treatment is completed. Extended Care is usually ranges from 3-6 months and helps make that commitment to change last.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Halfway Houses", "halfway_houses", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>A halfway house is a facility that accommodates individuals battling alcoholism, drug addiction, mental illness and similar disorders. Some half way houses may specialize in different areas, such as alcoholism, drug addiction, mental illness, or released prisoners.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Mens Treatment Centers", "mens_treatment", "facilities") & @Html.ActionLink("Womens Treatment Centers", "womens_treatment", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>Gender specific treatment in the addiction and recovery industry is in high demand. These categories were created to assist those looking for gender specific programs tailored to the therapeutic needs of men or women. These facilities specialize and do not offer programs for men and women at the same location.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="com-md-12">
                    <h6>@Html.ActionLink("Sober Houses", "sober_houses", "facilities")</h6>
                    <p>A sober house is an inexpensive drug and alcohol- free environment where the alcoholic or drug addict can obtain support from peer groups. In general, the rules at a halfway house are stricter than the rules at a sober house (sometimes called a 3/4 house).</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@*For autocomplete*@
<script type="text/javascript">
    function autocomplete() {
        var autocomplete;
        var input = document.getElementById('Address');
        var options = {
            componentRestrictions: { country: 'us' }
        };
        autocomplete = new google.maps.places.Autocomplete(input, options);
    }

    function loadScript() {
        var script = document.createElement('script');
        script.type = 'text/javascript';
        script.src = 'https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?v=3.exp&signed_in=true&libraries=places&callback=autocomplete';
        document.body.appendChild(script);
    }

    window.onload = loadScript;

</script>